U.K. military action against
Muammar Qaddafiâ€™s regime in  Libya  is supported by 35 percent of
British adults, while 43 percent oppose it, according to a
ComRes Ltd. poll for ITV News.  The survey found that 53 percent of respondents said it was
unacceptable for members of the British armed forces to risk
injury or death to protect the Libyan opposition, ComRes said in
an e-mailed statement today. The poll questioned 2,028 adults
between March 18 and March 20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
